ENTRY       EC 3.4.22.8                 Enzyme
NAME        clostripain;
            clostridiopeptidase B;
            clostridium histolyticum proteinase B;
            alpha-clostridipain;
            clostridiopeptidase
CLASS       Hydrolases;
            Acting on peptide bonds (peptidases);
            Cysteine endopeptidases
REACTION    Preferential cleavage: Arg!, including Arg!Pro, but not Lys-
COMMENT     From the bacterium Clostridium histolyticum. It requires Ca2+ ions and is inhibited by EDTA. Type example of peptidase family C11.
HISTORY     EC 3.4.22.8 created 1961 as EC 3.4.4.20, transferred 1972 to EC 3.4.22.8
